    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-yuzu-basa-with-rice-and-sesame-slaw/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden and cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-yuzu-basa-with-rice-and-sesame-slaw/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>and chop it into bite-sized pieces \u2013 this is your <strong>smacked cucumber</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-yuzu-basa-with-rice-and-sesame-slaw/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix </strong>and <strong>smacked cucumber</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-yuzu-basa-with-rice-and-sesame-slaw/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-yuzu-basa-with-rice-and-sesame-slaw/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>yuzu dressing </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your<strong> shichimi togarashi </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>to a small bowl with 50m<span class=\"text-purple\">l [75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> firecracker yuzu sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-yuzu-basa-with-rice-and-sesame-slaw/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the basa is cooked through, add the<strong> firecracker yuzu sauce</strong> and cook for 1 min or until slightly thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>firecracker yuzu basa</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/firecracker-yuzu-basa-with-rice-and-sesame-slaw/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>firecracker yuzu basa </strong>with the <strong>cooked rice </strong>and <strong>sesame slaw </strong>to the side</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining shichimi togarashi</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
